lign: center;\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/03/21/theater/reviews/breakfast-at-tiffanys-starring-emilia-clarke.html |title=More Waifish Than Wild, the Ing\u00e9nue Returns |last=Brantley |first=Ben |date=20 March 2013 |website=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[A. G. Sulzberger]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160901123724/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/03/21/theater/reviews/breakfast-at-tiffanys-starring-emilia-clarke.html |archive-date=1 September 2016 |access-date=20 November 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020\n! scope=row data-sort-value=\"Seagull, The\" | ''[[The Seagull]]''\n|Nina\n| [[Playhouse Theatre]]\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/12/emilia-clarke-seagull-west-end-london-stage-debut-game-of-thrones-1202814901/ |title='Game Of Thrones' Emilia Clarke Sets Chekhov's 'The Seagull' For London Stage Debut |last=Evans |first=Greg |date=20 December 2019 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191220173015/https://deadline.com/2019/12/emilia-clarke-seagull-west-end-london-stage-debut-game-of-thrones-1202814901/ |archive-date=20 December 2019 |access-date=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Emilia Clarke}}\nClarke has been nominated for numerous awards throughout her career. She was nominated for four [[Primetime Emmy Awards]], including [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series]] in 2019, for her role in ''Game of Thrones''.<ref name=\"thewrapemmy\">{{Cite news |last=Jennifer |first=Maas |url=https://www.thewrap.com/emmy-nominations-2019-list-emmys-nominees/ |title=Emmy Nominees 2019: The Complete List |date=22 September 2019 |work=[[TheWrap]] |access-date=30 January 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031112423/https://www.thewrap.com/emmy-nominations-2019-list-emmys-nominees/ |archive-date=31 October 2019 |last2=Maglio |first2=Tony}}</ref> She has received several [[Broadcast Film Critics Association Award|Critics' Choice Awards]] nominations.The most recent one in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2018-critics-choice-awards-nominations-list-full-1062824/item/best-picture-critics-choice-nominations-2018-1062858|title=Best Picture - Critics' Choice Awards: 'The Shape of Water' Leads With 14 Nominations|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref> She also received the [[BAFTA]] [[Britannia Awards|Britannia Award]] for British Artist of the Year at the [[Britannia Awards#2010%E2%80%93present|2018 ceremony]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/2018/britannias/britannia-award-for-british-artist-of-the-year |title=2018 Britannias Britannia Award for British Artist of the Year {{!}} BAFTA Awards |website=BAFTA |publisher=[[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] |access-date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Honours ===\nIn 2018, Clarke was invited to join the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oscars.org/news/academy-invites-928-membership|title=ACADEMY INVITES 928 TO MEMBERSHIP|date=25 June 2018|website=Oscars.org {{!}} Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|language=en|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref> [[Time (magazine)|Time]] magazine named her one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people]] in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/04/24/entertainment/gallery/time-100-gala/index.html|title=TIME most influential people of 2019, in pictures|website=CNN|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref> Clarke has also been honoured for her charitable work. In 2019, she won a [[Shorty Awards|Shorty Award]] for a video that was made to raise awareness for her charity SameYou and the [[Royal College of Nursing]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://shortyawards.com/4th-socialgood/emilia-clarke-x-omaze|title=Emilia Clarke x Omaze - The Shorty Awards|date=16 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316141321/https://shortyawards.com/4th-socialgood/emilia-clarke-x-omaze|access-date=10 April 2020|archive-date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = [[List of awards and nominations received by Emilia Clarke|Awards for Emilia Clarke]]\n|list =\n{{BAFTA Los Angeles Britannia Awards}}\n{{Saturn Award for Best Actress on Television}}\n}}\n\n{{portalbar|Biography|Film}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Clarke, Emilia}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century English actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Berkshire]]\n[[Category:Actresses from London]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Oxfordshire]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Drama Centre London]]\n[[Category:English film actresses]]\n[[Category:English stage actresses]]\n[[Category:English television actresses]]\n[[Category:English voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People educated at Rye St Antony School]]\n[[Category:People educated at St Edward's School, Oxford]]\n[[Category:English people of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:Stroke survivors]]\n", "name_user": "The ed17", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e''Game of Thrones'' and rise to international prominence (2011\u20132019):WP:EGG", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emilia_Clarke"}
{"title_page": "Adelolecia", "text_new": "{{Taxobox\n| image =\n| image_caption =\n| regnum = [[Fungi]]\n| divisio = [[Ascomycota]]\n| classis = [[Lecanoromycetes]]\n| ordo = [[Lecanorales]]\n| familia = [[Ramalinaceae]]\n| genus = '''''Adelolecia'''''\n| genus_authority = Hertel & Hafellner<ref>{{cite journal |author=Hafellner J. |year=1984 |title=Studien in Richtung einer nat\u00fcrlichen Gliederung der Sammelfamilien Lecanoracae und Lecideaceae |journal=Beihefte zur Nova Hedwigia |volume=79 |issue= |pages=241\u2013371|language=German}}</ref>\n| type_species = ''[[Adelolecia pilati]]'' \n| type_species_authority = Hertel & Hafellner\n| subdivision_ranks = [[Species]]\n| subdivision = ''A. kolaensis''<br>\n''A. rhododendrina''<br>\n''A. sonorae''\n}}\n\n'''''Adelolecia''''' is a [[genus]] of [[lichen]]ized fungi in the family [[Ramalinaceae]].<ref>{{cite journal|last=Lumbsch TH, Huhndorf SM. |date=December 2007 |title=Outline of Ascomycota \u2013 2007 |journal=Myconet |volume=13 |pages=1\u201358 |url=http://archive.fieldmuseum.org/myconet/outline.asp |publisher=The Field Museum, Department of Botany |location=Chicago, USA |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090318003134/http://www.fieldmuseum.org/myconet/outline.asp |archivedate=2009-03-18 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*''[http://www.indexfungorum.org/Names/genusrecord.asp?RecordID=78 Adelolecia]'' at [[Index Fungorum]]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q4682017}}\n\n[[Category:Ramalinaceae]]\n[[Category:Lichens]]\n\n\n{{Lecanoromycetes-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Taxobox\n| image =\n| image_caption =\n| regnum = [[Fungi]]\n| divisio = [[Ascomycota]]\n| classis = [[Lecanoromycetes]]\n| ordo = [[Lecanorales]]\n| familia = [[Ramalinaceae]]\n| genus = '''''Adelolecia'''''\n| genus_authority = Hertel & Hafellner<ref>{{cite journal |author=Hafellner J. |year=1984 |title=Studien in Richtung einer nat\u00fcrlichen Gliederung der Sammelfamilien Lecanoracae und Lecideaceae |journal=Bei