ew Jersey]]\n\n====NY====\n*[[The Strong]], [[International Center for the History of Electronic Games]], [[Rochester, NY]] - Focus on [[Retrogaming]] but many games are on vintage personal computers.\n====PA====\n*[[Large Scale Systems Museum]], [[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania]]\n====RI====\n*[[Rhode Island Computer Museum]], [[North Kingstown, Rhode Island]]\n====TX====\n*Brazos Valley Computer Museum, [[Bryan, Texas]]<ref>{{cite web|title=A locally curated collection of old computers|url=http://bv-computer-museum.org|website=www.bv-comptuer-museum.org|accessdate=3 March 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Museum of Computer Culture]], [[Austin, Texas]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Power up the Past!|url=http://www.computerculture.org/|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>\n*[[National Videogame Museum]], [[Frisco, Texas]]<ref>{{cite web|title=National Videogame Museum|url=http://www.nvmusa.org/our-mission|website=www.nvmusa.org|accessdate=25 September 2017}}</ref>\n\n====VA====\n*[[U.Va. Computer Museum]], [[University of Virginia]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The U.Va. Computer Museum|url=https://www.cs.virginia.edu/about/museum/|website=www.cs.virginia.edu|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>\n====WA====\n*[[Living Computer Museum]], [[Seattle, Washington]]\n*[[Microsoft Visitor Center]], [[Redmond, Washington]]\n\n\n\n==South America==\n===Argentina===\n*[[Museo de Inform\u00e1tica UNPA-UARG]], [[R\u00edo Gallegos]] - [https://www.uarg.unpa.edu.ar/imuseo/ Official Website]\n*[[Museo de Inform\u00e1tica de la Rep\u00fablica Argentina - Fundaci\u00f3n ICATEC]], [[Ciudad Aut\u00f3noma de Buenos Aires]] - [https://museodeinformatica.org.ar/ Official Website]\n\n==Online==\n*Old Computer Museum - [http://www.oldcomputermuseum.com/default.html]\n*San Diego Computer Museum - [http://www.computer-museum.org/ Official Website] - Physical objects were donated to the [[San Diego State University]] Library, but still does online exhibits\n*Obsolete Computer Museum- [http://obsoletecomputermuseum.org/ Official Website]\n*Old-Computers.com - [https://www.old-computers.com/news/default.asp Official Website]\n*HP Computer Museum - [http://www.hpmuseum.net/index.php Official Website]\n*Early Office Museum - [http://www.officemuseum.com/data_processing_machines.htm Official Website]\n*[[IBM]] Archives - [http://www-03.ibm.com/ibm/history/ Official Website]\n*EveryMac.com - [http://www.everymac.com/ Official Website]\n*Bitsavers.org - [http://bitsavers.trailing-edge.com/ Official Website] - Software and Document Archive\n*TAM (The [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] Museum) - [http://theapplemuseum.org/html/main/home.html Official Website] - Apple Computers and Products \n*Rewind Museum - [http://www.rewindmuseum.com/tours.htm Official Website] - Virtual museum with traveling physical exhibits\n*[[Virtual Museum of Computing]] \n* The Computer Collector - [http://www.computercollector.com/ Official Website]\n*New Computer Museum - [https://newcomputermuseum.org/ Official Website]\n*IPSJ Computer Museum - [http://museum.ipsj.or.jp/en/about/index.html Official Website] - Computers of Japan\n* MOCA - Museum of Computer Art - [http://moca.virtual.museum/index.asp Official Website]\n* Freeman PC Museum - [http://www.thepcmuseum.net/ Official Website]\n* FEMICOM Museum - [http://www.femicom.org/about/index.php Official Website] - Femininity in 20th century Video games, computers and electronic toys\n* Home Computer Museum - [http://www.homecomputer.de/pages/f_new.html Official Website]\n* Malware Museum - [https://archive.org/details/malwaremuseum&tab=about  Official Website] - Malware programs from the 80's and 90's that have been stripped of their destructive properties.\n*History Computers - [http://history-computer.com Official Website]\n* KASS Computer Museum - [http://kartsci.org/kocomu/ Official Website] - A computer history museum & private collection\n* Russian Virtual Computer Museum - [http://www.computer-museum.ru Official Website]- a history of Soviet Computers from the late 1940s\n* Soviet Digital Electronics Museum - [http://www.leningrad.su/museum/ Official Website] - a museum of Soviet electronic calculators, PCs and some other devices\n*Development of Computer Science and Technologies in Ukraine - [http://www.icfcst.kiev.ua/MUSEUM/museum-map.html Official Website] - Ukrainian virtual Computer Museum\n*[https://www.spectrumgeneration.com Spectrum Generation] collection, supporting the [https://www.loadzx.com LOAD ZX Spectrum] Museum in Portugal\n\n==See also==\n* [[Computer museum]]\n* [[List of video game museums]]\n\n==References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Computer museums}}\n[[Category:History of computing]]\n[[Category:Lists of museums by subject]]\n[[Category:Computer museums|*]]\n[[Category:Video game museums]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nBelow is a '''list of [[computer museum]]s''' around the world, organized by continent and country, then alphabetically by location. \n{{expand list|date=August 2016}}\n\n==Asia==\n\n===South Korea===\n* [[Nexon Computer Museum]]\n\n==Australia==\n*[[The Australian Computer Museum Society, Inc]], [[NSW]] - very large collection|url=http://www.acms.org.au/}}</ref>\n*[[The Nostalgia Box]], [[Perth]] - Video Game Museum<ref>{{cite web|title=TheNostalgiaBox|url=http://thenostalgiabox.com.au/|website=thenostalgiabox.com.au|accessdate=6 September 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Powerhouse Museum]] - Has Computer Exhibit\n*[[Monash Museum of Computing History]], [[Monash University]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Monash Museum of Computing History|url=http://www.infotech.monash.edu.au/about/museum/}}</ref>\n\n==Europe==\n\n===Belgium===\n* [http://www.nam-ip.be/ Computermuseum NAM-IP], Namur\n\n===Croatia===\n*[[Peek&Poke]], [[Rijeka]]<ref>{{cite web|title=PEEK&POKE Muzej Ra\u010dunala - Computer Museum|url=http://www.peekpoke.hr/welcome/|website=www.peekpoke.hr}}</ref>\n\n===Czech Republic===\n*[[Apple Museum, Prague]] [http://www.applemuseum.com/en/]\n\n===Finland===\n*[[Rupriikki Media Muse