, [[Munich]] - Large computer collection in their Communications exhibit\n*[[technikum29 living museum]], [[Frankfurt]] - Working and under restoration.\n*[[Computerarchiv Muenchen]], [http://computerarchiv-muenchen.de], [[Munich]] - Computer, Video Games and Magazine Archive<ref>{{cite web|title=Computerarchiv Muenchen : s\u00fcddeutsches Museum f\u00fcr digitale Entwicklungsgeschichte|url=http://d-nb.info/1205810919|website=Deutsche Nationalbibliothek}}</ref>\n*[[:de:Computermuseum der Fachhochschule Kiel|Computermuseum der Fachhochschule Kiel]], [[Kiel]]\n*[[:de:Analog Computer Museum]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Analog Computer Museum|url=http://analogmuseum.org/|website=analogmuseum.org}}</ref> [[Bad Schwalbach / Hettenhain]] - Large collection of analog computers, working and under restoration.\n\n===Greece===\n*[https://elmp.gr/en/home_en/ Hellenic IT Museum]\n\n===Ireland===\n* [[Computer and Communications Museum of Ireland]], [[National University of Ireland]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Computer and Communications Museum of Ireland {{!}} MSPI Participants {{!}} Museums Standards Programme for Ireland {{!}} Our Initiatives {{!}} Museums and Archive {{!}} The Heritage Council|url=http://www.heritagecouncil.ie/museums-archive/heritage-council-initiatives/museums-standards-programme-for-ireland/mspi-participants/computer-and-communications-museum-of-ireland/|website=www.heritagecouncil.ie|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Israel===\n*[[The Israeli Personal Computer Museum]], [[Haifa]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Israeli Personal Computer Museum Page|url=http://www.ipcm.org.il/index_eng.html/|website=http://www.ipcm.org.il/index_eng.html}}</ref>\n\n===Italy===\n*[[UNESCO Computer Museum]], [[Padova]]<ref>{{cite web|title=FWT UNESCO Computer Museum Home Page|url=http://musi.fwtunesco.org/|website=musi.fwtunesco.org}}</ref>\n*[[All About Apple Museum]], [[Savona]]<ref>{{cite web|title=All About Apple Museum - The alive Apple Museum in Italy|url=https://www.allaboutapple.com/en/|website=All About Apple}}</ref>\n*[[Video Game Museum of Rome|VIGAMUS]], [[Rome]] - Video Game Museum\n*[http://www.museotecnologicamente.it/the-tecnologicmente-museum-workshop-in-ivrea/ Tecnologic@mente, Ivrea]\n*[https://www.msc.sma.unipi.it/ Museo degli strumenti per il calcolo, Pisa]\n\n===The Netherlands===\n* [http://www.applemuseum-nederland.nl/ Apple Museum Nederland], Orvelte near Hoogeveen\n* [http://www.spelcomputermuseum.nl/ Bonami SpelComputer Museum], Zwolle\n* [https://ub.fnwi.uva.nl/computermuseum/ Computer Museum Universiteit van Amsterdam], Amsterdam<ref>{{cite web|title=UvA Computermuseum|url=https://ub.fnwi.uva.nl/computermuseum//|website=ub.fnwi.uva.nl}}</ref>\n* [http://museum.hack42.nl/ Computermuseum Hack42], Arnhem\n* [https://www.homecomputermuseum.nl HomeComputerMuseum], [[Helmond]] <ref>{{cite web|title=HomeComputerMuseum|url=https://www.homecomputermuseum.nl//|website=www.homecomputermuseum.nl}}</ref> \n* [http://www.rotterdamsradiomuseum.nl/de-afdelingen/computers-en-telecom/ Rotterdams Radio Museum], Rotterdam\n* [http://www.bejaardecomputers.nl/ Tehuis voor Bejaarde Computers], Winssen near Nijmegen\n\n===Poland===\n*[[Muzeum Historii Komputer\u00f3w i Informatyki]], [[Katowice]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Muzeum Historii Komputer\u00f3w i Informatyki Home Page|url=http://www.muzeumkomputerow.edu.pl/|website=www.muzeumkomputerow.edu.pl}}</ref>\n\n=== Portugal ===\n\n*[https://www.loadzx.com LOAD ZX Spectrum Museum], Cantanhede\n\n===Russia===\n*[[Museum of Soviet Arcade Machines]], [[Moscow]]\n*[https://yandex.ru/museum/ Yandex Museum, Moscow] \n*[http://apple-museum.ru Moscow Apple Museum]\n*[[Museum of computers]], [[Yekaterinburg]]\n\n===Slovenia===\n* Computer Museum [[Dru\u0161tvo Ra\u010dunalni\u0161ki Muzej]], [[Ljubljana]]\n\n===Spain===\n*[[Computer Museum Garcia Santesmases]] (MIGS), [[Complutense University]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Complutense University of Madrid|url=https://www.ucm.es/english/computer|website=www.ucm.es}}</ref>\n*[[Museum of Informatics]], [[Polytechnic University of Valencia]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Museum of Informatics|url=http://museo.inf.upv.es/en|website=www.upv.es}}</ref>\n*http://www.museoapple.com/\n\n===Switzerland===\n*[[Mus\u00e9e Bolo]], [[Lausanne]]\n*Enter-Museum, Solothurn [http://www.enter-online.ch/index.php?id=taetigkeit]\n\n===Ukraine===\n*[https://sncmuseum.org Software & Computer Museum], [[Kyiv]], [[Kharkiv]]\n\n===United Kingdom===\n*[[The National Museum of Computing]], [[Bletchley Park]]\n*[[The Centre for Computing History]], [[Cambridge]] \n*[[Retro Computer Museum]], [[Leicester]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Retro Computer Museum|url=http://www.retrocomputermuseum.co.uk|website=www.retrocomputermuseum.co.uk}}</ref>\n*[[Science Museum, London]], [[London]]\n*[[National Archive for the History of Computing]], [[University of Manchester]]<ref>{{cite web|title=http://www.chstm.manchester.ac.uk/research/nahc/|url=http://www.chstm.manchester.ac.uk/research/nahc/|access-date=2016-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120113015243/http://www.chstm.manchester.ac.uk/research/nahc/|archive-date=2012-01-13|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*[[National Videogame Arcade]], [[Nottingham]]\n*[[The Computing Futures Museum]], [[Staffordshire University]] - In association with the [[British Computer Society|BCS]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Staffordshire University Computing Futures Museum Home Page - a computer hardware museum/ teaching resource on the Stafford campus of Staffordshire University, The Octagon, Beaconside, Stafford, Staffordshire, UK|url=http://www.fcet.staffs.ac.uk/jdw1/sucfm/index.html|website=www.fcet.staffs.ac.uk}}</ref>\n*[[Museum of Computing]], [[Swindon]]\n*[[Time Line Computer Archive]], [[Wigton]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Time Line Computer Archive|url=http://t-lcarchive.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1145&Itemid=471|website=t-lcarchive.org}}</ref>\n*[[The Micro Museum]], [[Ramsgate]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Micro Museum - Computer Museum - Ramsgate Kent UK|url=http://www.themicromuseum.org/about-us|website=The Micro Museum - Computer Museum - Ramsgate Kent UK|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Home Computer Museum]], [[Kingston upon Hull|Hull]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Home Computer Museum - Hull, Humberside UK|url=http://www.homecomputermuseum.co.uk|website=www.homecomputermuseum.co.uk}}</ref>\n\nSee also: [[Computer Conservation Society]]<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.computerconservationsociety.org/museums.htm | title=UK Computer Museums | publisher=[[Computer Conservation Society]] | location=UK | accessdate=2 September 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==North America==\n\n===Canada===\n*[[Personal Computer Museum]], [[Brantford]]\n*[[iMus\u00e9e]], [[Montreal]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imusee.net/}}</ref>\n*[[York University Computer Museum]] or YUCoM, [[York University]]\n*[[Nova Scotia First Museum]], [[Annapolis Royal]]\n*[https://computermuseum.usask.ca/ University of Saskatchewan Computer Museum]\n\n===United States===\n====AZ====\n*[[Southwest Museum of Engineering,Communications and Computation]], [[Glendale, Arizona]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Southwest Museum Of Engineering, Communications and Computation -Arizona's Radio and Television Museum - Also History Of Computers andComputation (SMECC)|url=http://www.smecc.org|website=www.smecc.org}}</ref>\n====CA====\n*[[Computer History Museum]], [[Mountain View, California]] \n*[[DigiBarn Computer Museum]], [[Boulder Creek, California]] \n*[[Museum of Art and Digital Entertainment]], [[Oakland, California]] \n*[[The Tech Museum of Innovation]], [[San Jose, California]] \n*[[Intel Museum]], [[Santa Clara, California]] \n====DC====\n*[[Smithsonian National Museum of American History]], [[Washington, D.C.]] \n====GA====\n*[[The Computer Museum of America]], [[Roswell, Georgia]], opened in 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.computermuseumofamerica.com/|title=Computer Museum of America}}</ref>\n\n====KS====\n*[[The Topeka Computing Museum]], 